#### **(b)** Write the Arduino code for the ESP32 trainer kit to read temperature from a DHT11 sensor and publish it to a local MQTT broker every 5 seconds. **(7 marks)** `[KTU University Exam - May 2024]`

**Model Solution:**

```cpp
#include <WiFi.h>
#include <PubSubClient.h>
#include <DHT.h>

#define DHTPIN   4
#define DHTTYPE  DHT11
const char* ssid       = "KTU_LAB";
const char* password   = "lab123";
const char* mqttServer = "192.168.1.10";
const int   mqttPort   = 1883;
const char* topic      = "iot/lab/temp";

DHT dht(DHTPIN, DHTTYPE);
WiFiClient wifiClient;
PubSubClient client(wifiClient);
unsigned long lastMsg = 0;
const long interval = 5000;

void setup() {
  Serial.begin(115200);
  dht.begin();
  WiFi.begin(ssid, password);
  while (WiFi.status() != WL_CONNECTED) { delay(500); Serial.print("."); }
  Serial.println("Wi-Fi connected");
  client.setServer(mqttServer, mqttPort);
}

void loop() {
  client.loop();
  if (millis() - lastMsg > interval) {
    lastMsg = millis();
    float t = dht.readTemperature();
    if (isnan(t)) { Serial.println("DHT read failed"); return; }
    char payload[64];
    snprintf(payload, sizeof(payload), "{\"temp\":%.1f}", t);
    client.publish(topic, payload);
    Serial.println(payload);
  }
}
```

**Code Explanation (for full 7 marks):**
- Library inclusion (`WiFi.h`, `PubSubClient.h`, `DHT.h`) — 1 mark.
- Wi-Fi connection logic — 1 mark.
- MQTT broker configuration — 1 mark.
- Sensor read and validation (`isnan` check) — 1 mark.
- JSON payload construction — 1 mark.
- `client.publish()` call — 1 mark.
- Timing logic with `millis()` and 5-second interval — 1 mark.

